data.content:
Gravitational waves are invisible (yet incredibly fast) ripples in space. The most powerful are created when objects move at very high speeds, like when a star explodes (supernova).

 Supernova Remnant W49B. X-ray: NASA/CXC/MIT/L.Lopez https://t.co/lOzTsftjCz
